<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1367,1554]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,326,1367,1393]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Observations:</emphasis>
The nomenclatural history of this species is highly controversial. In early studies, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cei &amp; Scolaro" firstAuthor="Cei" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="225 - 226" refId="ref55342" refString="Cei, J. M. &amp; Scolaro, J. A. (1977 a) Herpetologia patagonica. XIII. La identidad de Liolaemus goetschi y de la forma melanops del grupo Liolaemus fitzingeri, en Rio Negro y Chubut. Physis, Buenos Aires, 36, 225 - 226." type="journal article" year="1977" yearSuffix="a">Cei &amp; Scolaro (1977a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cei &amp; Scolaro" box="[306,379,1408,1434]" firstAuthor="Cei" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="15 - 16" refId="ref55614" refString="Cei, J. M. &amp; Scolaro, J. A. (1983 a) Un nuevo arreglo taxonomico para los Liolaemus del grupo fitzingeri. Boletin de la Asociacion Herpetologica Argentina, 1, 15 - 16." type="journal article" year="1983" yearSuffix="a">1983a</bibRefCitation>
) placed this taxon into the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Etheridge" authorityYear="1993" box="[884,1030,1408,1433]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanops">
<emphasis box="[884,1030,1408,1433]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">L. melanops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Etheridge &amp; Espinoza" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Etheridge" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref59521" refString="Etheridge, R &amp; Espinoza, R. E. (2000) Taxonomy of the Liolaeminae (Squamata: Iguania: Tropiduridae) and a semiannotated bibliography. Smithsonian Herpetological Information Service, 126, 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="2000">
Etheridge &amp; Espinoza 
<emphasis box="[1374,1436,1408,1433]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2000
</bibRefCitation>
). However, in a recent work, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cei &amp; Scolaro" box="[556,806,1448,1474]" firstAuthor="Cei" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="107 - 112" refId="ref72364" refString="Scolaro, J. A. &amp; Cei, J. M. (2003) Una excepcional nueva especie de Phymaturus de la precordillera de Chubut, Argentina (Liolaemidae, Iguania, Lacertilia, Reptilia). Facena, 19, 107 - 112." type="journal article" year="2003">Cei &amp; Scolaro (2003)</bibRefCitation>
provided evidence to support the idea that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Hellmich" authorityYear="1938" box="[1308,1436,1448,1473]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goetschi">
<emphasis box="[1308,1436,1448,1473]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">L. goetschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a valid species independent from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Etheridge" authorityYear="1993" box="[581,726,1488,1513]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanops">
<emphasis box="[581,726,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">L. melanops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Abdala" box="[792,949,1488,1514]" firstAuthor="Abdala" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref50199" refString="Abdala, C. S. (2007) Phylogeny of the boulengeri group (Iguania: Liolaemidae, Liolaemus) based on morphological and molecular characters. Zootaxa, 1538, 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="2007">Abdala 2007</bibRefCitation>
). See also comments provided below for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abdala" authorityYear="2003" box="[151,377,1528,1553]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="martorii">
<emphasis box="[151,377,1528,1553]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Liolaemus martorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
